# Tone of Voice - [COMPANY NAME]

## Voice Attributes (4-5 characteristics)

Describe each attribute as a spectrum: [what we do], not [what we avoid].

1. **[e.g. Direct]** - We say what works, without hedging or filler. Not: aggressive or rude.
2. **[e.g. Evidence-based]** - Every claim has proof or an example. Not: dry and boring.
3. **[e.g. Expert but accessible]** - We write for experts, but to inform, not to impress. Not: academic or gatekeeping.
4. **[e.g. Practical]** - Every article must give the reader something actionable today. Not: purely theoretical.
5. **[optional, e.g. Candid]** - We acknowledge when something is hard or uncertain. Not: salesy.

